[21:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'super fun. We came across some interesting news from the team at Nvidia this last week, where they\'ve developed a real-time generative AI framework for taking characters and having them'

[21:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually interact with their environment in a gaming context. Long story short, whenever you are playing a video game and a character comes across, let\'s say, an object or a surface, a lot of times the animation that\'s applied to the'

[22:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'character whenever you actually interact, it\'s predefined. It\'s usually pulling from some sort of motion library. However, the way they\'ve coded the system is to take 350,000 motion clips and create AI motion in'

[22:15] [scene:talk]
